{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599542","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599542"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:56:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:56:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15579"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15579","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15579"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.05,0.48,0.24,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8270"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67107"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8270","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8270"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15579"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52562"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"8707"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19976"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19978"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22451"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67107","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67107"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring embryological development, the parathyroid glands form from specific pharyngeal pouches.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"From which of the following pouches do the parathyroid glands develop?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["First and second","Second and third","Third and fourth","Fourth and fifth","Fifth and sixth"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe parathyroid glands develop from the \u003Cstrong\u003Ethird and fourth pharyngeal pouches\u003C/strong\u003E during embryological development. The \u003Cstrong\u003Esecond and third pouches\u003C/strong\u003E are not involved in parathyroid development - the second pouch gives rise to the palatine tonsils. The \u003Cstrong\u003Efirst and second pouches\u003C/strong\u003E form the auditory tube and palatine tonsils respectively. The \u003Cstrong\u003Efourth and fifth pouches\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Efifth and sixth pouches\u003C/strong\u003E are incorrect combinations - the fifth pouch is rudimentary in humans, while the sixth pouch gives rise to the ultimobranchial body.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003ESpecifically:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EThe superior parathyroid glands develop from the fourth pharyngeal pouch\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EThe inferior parathyroid glands develop from the third pharyngeal pouch\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EThis embryological origin explains their final anatomical positions\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The parathyroid glands develop from the third and fourth pharyngeal pouches during embryological development","The superior parathyroid glands arise from the fourth pharyngeal pouch","The inferior parathyroid glands arise from the third pharyngeal pouch"],"references":["Lofrese JJ, Basit H, Lappin SL. Physiology, Parathyroid. [Updated 2023 Jul 17]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482510/","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical